data.title: The Metropolitan Museum of Art
data.text:
Director and CEO Max Hollein celebrates an important moment as the Museum moves forward with renovation plans for the new Oscar L. and H.M. Agnes Hsu-Tang Wing with architect Frida Escobedo, the first woman to design a wing in the Museums 154-year history.

What happens when intimate possessions end up in art museums? Find out in this new episode of The Mets podcast.

Met Members enjoy a rich variety of specialized benefitsfrom free guest passes to Member Preview Days for new exhibitionsall while supporting our mission.
